<h2>Introduction</h2>

<p>Boost.Build's <a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/visualc/">vc7</a> toolset supports the
Microsoft Visual C++ .NET tools. This toolset is an extention to the
<code><a href="msvc-tools.html">msvc</a></code> toolset and is usefull for when
you need to have access to both version 6 and version 7 of the toolsets.

<h2>Configuration Variables</h2>

The vc7 toolset responds to the following variables which can be set in the
environment or configured on the jam command-line using
<code>-s<i>VARIABLE_NAME</i>=</code><i>value</i>:

<table border="1">

<tr><th>Variable Name <th>Semantics <th>Default <th>Notes

<tr>
    <td><code>VC7_ROOT</code>
    <td>Path to installation of VC7.
    <td><code>C:\Program&nbsp;Files\Microsoft&nbsp;Visual&nbsp;Studio&nbsp;.NET\VC7</code>
    <td>If <code>MSVCDir</code> is set in the environment, the toolset
    will assume <code>VCVARS32.BAT</code>has already been called, and
    will ignore this variable.

</table>

